    q: "What is OPL (on-premise laundry) and how is it different from coin laundry or industrial laundry?",
    a: "OPL is on-site laundry equipment owned and operated by a single facility for its own linens, uniforms, or towels. Hotels wash room sheets and towels in-house, hospitals wash patient linens, senior care does resident bedding. Different from coin laundromats (self-service public) and industrial contract laundries (multiple-facility throughput). OPL machines run 30 to 80 lb capacity, 8 to 16 hour daily cycles, dependable uptime is critical.",
