<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">OPL service</p>
    <h2>On-premise laundry uptime is the difference between guests with clean towels and a 200-room hotel that just lost service.</h2>

    <p>OPL (on-premise laundry) is the laundry equipment your facility owns and runs in-house: hotel rooms' sheets and towels, hospital linens, senior care bedding, restaurant uniforms and napery. Different category from a public laundromat (coin/vended) and from an industrial contract laundry serving multiple facilities. OPL machines run 30 to 80 lb capacity, 8 to 16 hour daily cycles, and dependable uptime is critical because the operation depends on processing yesterday's load before tonight's check-ins.</p>

    <p>Our techs service the full OPL lineup across LA County, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, Riverside. <strong>Speed Queen Quantum</strong> commercial line (SC30, SC60, SC80, the LA hotel and senior care default). <strong>UniMac</strong> (UW80, UW100, premium hospital and university tier, Alliance Laundry sister brand to Speed Queen). <strong>Continental Girbau</strong> EH-Series high-extract (EH075, EH090, Spanish independent, popular in healthcare for water-extraction efficiency). <strong>Maytag Commercial Laundry</strong> (Whirlpool Corp, mid-tier OPL).</p>

    <p>$120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. <strong>BHGS #A49573</strong> license. <strong>EPA 608 Universal certified #1346255700410</strong>. <strong>CSLB C-20 HVAC</strong> scope for adjacent commercial gas dryer and steam-system work. BBB A+. Phones answered 24/7. Parent: <a href="/commercial/washer-repair/">commercial washer repair</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Common scenarios</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Top OPL repairs in our 5-county territory.</h2>
    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Drain pump (year 4 to 6).</strong> Heavy detergent residue plus lint accumulates in the pump impeller. Replace $360 to $540.</li>
      <li><strong>Door interlock switch.</strong> High cycle count wear (the door opens and closes 50+ times per day in busy OPL). $260 to $420.</li>
      <li><strong>Inlet valves (hot, cold, auto-fill solenoids).</strong> LA hard water deposits scale on the diaphragm. Often replace as a set. $300 to $480.</li>
      <li><strong>Drive motor and belt.</strong> High spin extraction stress. Belt wear at year 4 to 6, motor at year 8 to 12. $440 to $880.</li>
      <li><strong>Control board (Quantum touchscreen, year 5 to 8).</strong> Speed Queen and UniMac Quantum panels are the most common high-cost service item. $980 to $1,400 full replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Bearings (year 6 to 10 standard extract; year 6 to 9 high-extract Continental Girbau).</strong> High-load wear. $880 to $1,600 (often replace-vs-repair threshold).</li>
      <li><strong>Door gasket and boot seal.</strong> Chemical exposure from detergents degrades the rubber. $340 to $580.</li>
      <li><strong>Steam injection valve (steam-heated commercial dryers).</strong> Adjacent specialty trade often needed. $480 to $780.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Field observations</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Three things we see on OPL calls that aren't in the operator's manual.</h2>

    <p><strong>1. LA hard water destroys inlet valve diaphragms faster than the manual predicts.</strong> Speed Queen and UniMac OPL inlet valves are rated for 5 to 7 years in average water-hardness service. LA municipal water in much of the basin runs harder than the rating assumes, and inland counties (Inland Empire, parts of OC) push it further. We see year-3 inlet valve failures in San Fernando Valley and IE hotels at meaningful frequency. Add a softener at the inlet line if you can; if you can't, plan inlet valve replacement as a year-3-to-5 service item rather than year-5-to-7.</p>

    <p><strong>2. High-extract bearings wear earlier than standard-extract.</strong> Continental Girbau EH-Series and premium UniMac models use 300+ G-force extraction to remove more water before drying. The trade-off is bearing wear: year 6 to 9 vs year 8 to 12 on standard-extract Speed Queen Quantum. Operators tolerate it for the dryer-time and energy savings, but they should plan for the bearing replacement on the earlier schedule. Bearing replacement runs $880 to $1,400 plus labor on these machines.</p>

    <p><strong>3. Quantum touchscreen failures mostly trace to the membrane keypad sub-component.</strong> When a Speed Queen or UniMac Quantum panel goes black or flickers, the first diagnostic question is whether it's a power-board issue, a membrane keypad, or a full panel failure. About 60% of cases we see are the membrane keypad alone, which is a $200 to $360 sub-component swap rather than the $980 to $1,400 full panel replacement. Always diagnose before quoting the full panel.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
